<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Lopharia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lopharia" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Lopharia</taxonomicName>
species by its resupinate basidiocarps, a densely compact texture, a monomitic hyphal system and small basidiospores 7
<normalizedToken originalValue="–9(–">-9(-</normalizedToken>
10) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="holotype">
